text.paragraph:
Using an autoinjector that is not compatible for use with Mylan’s glatiramer acetate injection may increase the risk for medication errors, such as dose omission or administration of a partial dose [see 

                              Warnings and Precautions (5.7)

                           ].

Because glatiramer acetate can modify immune functions, concerns exist about its potential to alter naturally-occurring immune responses. There is no evidence that glatiramer acetate does this, but this has not been systematically evaluated [see 

                              Warnings and Precautions (5.5)

                           ].
